      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MARINES CRY (4) sat on the speed and ran away to score by 2.8L at this track last time out. Back to 1200m here, but with the speed she showed last start that shouldn't be an issue. Can find the front again from an inside barrier and repeat the dose. GOOD VIBES (3) settled midfield but ran over the top to score by 1L here first-up. Cheung's 3kg claim comes in handy now and he has a good record aboard the mare. Fitter now and she can get the job done again. PRETTY DEVINE (1) finished behind GOOD VIBES after leading the field here last time out. Webster's claim is a bonus to bring the weight down and the inside draw is likely to be on the speed. Can go one better without surprising. G'DAY BLOKE (6) will be fitter for that effort and he's a winner second-up in the past. Can improve. QUICK AS SILVER (7) is racing in good order and can feature.",
